{
  "texts": [
    "However, the LLMs considered in [2]- [4] are confined to processing a single mode of textual data, which restricts their role exclusively to network chatbots.",
    "Accordingly, such LLMs cannot capture the modality of the data rising from the multi-service functionalities (e.g., sensing, communication, etc.)",
    "of future wireless networks.",
    "Although the authors in [5] present a vision focused on utilizing multimodal LLMs, their approach relies on LLMs like GPT-x, LLaMA, or Falcon tailored for natural language processing (NLP) tasks.",
    "To become effective, such multi-modal LLMs must be fine-tuned to single, narrow wireless tasks such as resource allocation."
  ]
}